Aha! The critical issue is revealed: **"Releasing container with 0 children"**. The containers being released have no children! This means the sprites have already been removed from the container before we try to release it.

Looking back at the test code, I see the issue:

```javascript
if (container.children.includes(oldContainer)) {
  container.removeChild(oldContainer);
}
```

When we remove the container from its parent, the PIXI mock might be clearing the children. Let me check if the mock's removeChild implementation does this:

